reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really great laptop. Be careful about aftermarket peripherals.
reviews.reviewText: I had a very nice Asus Chromebook that was reaching its end of automatic updates life. I love the operating system, but this EAU stuff ticked me off big time and I decided to go with a W11 laptop.This is a VERY nice machine. Screen is beautiful, touchscreen and flip features work as expected. This is not my main computer, so 16Gb, 500 Gb SSD, and a Ryzen 5 5600H are just fine. It has a type C USB, HDMI out, and two USB A third generation connectors, as well as a headphones/mic thing. I'm not a gamer, but the screen is gorgeous and the computer is responsive. Keyboard is nice as well.There are a couple of caveats. These are not negatives, but might be something to consider when deciding what to buy.If you choose to get a keyboard cover, be very careful what you purchase. For an ASUS laptop, the layout is nonstandard. This is a TN3402QA. Make sure you get the right device.Second caveat has to do with power. It really likes to be charged with a dedicated charger rather than USBC. This is despite the USB C port clearly marked as power delivery capable. It would accept input from a UGreen 100W charger, and it didn't blow up, but it kept telling me that the charger was low power. If you do purchase a second power brick, this computer needs a 4.5mm barrel, 3.0mm inner diameter connector. Again, not typical for ASUS and it was a bit of a wild goose chase to buy a backup charger.All that said, I am extremely happy with this purchase. Great price point, great performance for my purposes, great screen

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had it for a full day so if something changes I will update my review, otherwise this was a great purchase. I got the 24gb ram and 1tb ssd and it runs perfectly so far.Pros:—2 in 1 laptop—Touchscreen is great and can be turned off if not wanting to use it—Fingerprint scanner on power button—Webcam Shield for privacy—Backlit keyboard (can be turned on and off)—Number pad on touch pad when needed (SO LOVING THAT)—Charges very quickly—Easy set up. If you know your way around windows and pc, you will have absolutely no problem setting this up without instructions.—Steam games run great—I have good internet but even then, this computer runs very quickly and pops up things immediately.Cons:—Battery life is not great, but I’ve seen that in reviews and from other people. It’s unfortunate but for me the pros of this laptop FAR outweigh this con.—Charger is a 2 piece, which is annoying on Asus.—Some stuff was pre installed and would cause pop-ups and had to uninstall a bunch of things I didn’t want but not a huge deal.—Fan is a little loud but not as loud as previous laptopsOverall I’m still rating it a 5 stars but closer to 4.5 because the pros outweigh the cons for me and because the seller was great when I had questions. Plus the did the upgrade on ram and ssd.
